main event: A UFO sighting occurred in Dolinsk, USSR in October 1957. The witness heard a tremendous sound and felt the house shaking, then saw a light high above in the western skies before it disappeared.
interesting points: The witness observed a strange flying object and described a tremendous sound accompanied by the house shaking.
The UFO sighting involved a single object observed from the ground.
Possible jet breaking sound barrier and disturbance to the atmosphere were mentioned in the comments.
The conclusion included 'insufficient data for evaluation' and 'probable balloon' as a possible explanation.
The witness was unable to identify the object and it disappeared shortly after being observed.
photographs: no photograph included in the report
